text: Jeremy Bingham (born 16 March 1936) is an Australian property businessman and Citizens' Reform Association politician. He was Lord Mayor of Sydney and an Alderman of the Sydney City Council from 1974 to 1991. He also was a member of the Hunter's Hill Municipal Council from 1965 to 1971. He was born in Gosford, New South Wales. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:Living people Category:Australian businesspeople Category:Politicians from Sydney
